{
  "texts": [
    "Prompt leaking attack is a method that involves inducing an LLM to output pre-designed instructions by providing user inputs, leaking sensitive information [208].",
    "It poses a significantly greater challenge compared to goal hijacking [130].",
    "Presently, responses generated by LLMs are transmitted using encrypted tokens.",
    "However, by employing certain algorithms and inferring token lengths based on packet sizes, it is possible to intercept privacy information exchanged between users and agents [179].",
    "User inputs, such as \"END."
  ]
}